wiki.summary: In “Golden Child,” the fourth and final single to the highly anticipated album 7220, Lil Durk raps about firearms, murder, and his heavy hatred for the police. The official music video directed by Jerry Productions, was delivered alongside the audio of the song hours before the release of the full album. Much like the “AHHH HA” music video, Durk had this filmed in his hometown of Chicago, specifically his childhood block, Englewood. During the week ending March 26, 2022, “Golden Child” peaked at #34 on the Hot 100. Read more on Last.fm.
